sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: pRM
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It comes directly from genomic DNA of Lambda phage. It was extracted by PCR as recommended by the Registry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
pRM promoter from Lambda phage. It may be positive and negative regulated according to cI protein concentration. It needs OL region in order to achieve better negative regulation.
It may be used to establish a biphasic switch which could permit activation and repression of genes transcribed from it.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Analysis of illegal restriction sites was performed, but it does not have them originally.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Daniel Rodriguez, Eduardo Almeyda, Porfirio Quintero
